column5: But we lost count of how many were whacking crank baits. Biggest was just under 20 inches. Most were      16-18.
nice job! Some beauty looking fish
Like a weed. They were very clean if not monsters.
And after a winter of basically spending most of my “mad money” exclusively on musky baits and building a new lure box to house them I  catch a very solid musky on…
I've caught my biggest walleyes fishing for musky, and my best musky fishing for walleye...lol
4 out of 5 biggest walleyes were up shallow on clear sunny days throwing chatterbaits and jerkbaits for bass...go figure looks like some very nice table fare there

Ain't that the truth. Caught my 1st Musky, sort of a Tiger, trolling a BLack Fury looking for a Pic, I said "Man I never saw a big Pike jump!!!" At least you guys boated a few, we got the Skunkeye yesterday.  Good to see the kid chuafering Pop's around.
Same on Saturday night. With another good walleye chop.
Very nice! You guys sure figured them out. BTW, GREAT hat. I've looked for a decent hat just like that but can't find one that fits me.
I don't wear them except fishing and hunting. That was a Bass pro purchase.
